  "hash": "SHA-256",
  "name": "N-PAMP transcript KAT",
  "profile": "Standard",
  "provenance": "Standards-derived, non-circular. The expected TH_* are produced by an INDEPENDENT byte-constructor (frame-type as 2-octet BE; each TLV as Type(2 BE)||Length(2 BE)||Value) followed by FIPS 180-4 SHA-256 — NOT by the N-PAMP Transcript type under test. The consuming test re-derives the points with its own manual constructor (oracle leg) AND with the real Transcript (impl leg); both MUST equal these values. SHA-256 itself is anchored to FIPS 180-4 via SHA-256(\"abc\"). The TLV values are deterministic KAT fixtures (not crypto-real); the transcript construction is value-agnostic, so this isolates byte-ordering, per-TLV granularity, and frame-type-only absorption (spec §3 / §7.1 divergence from RFC 8446 §4.4.1).",
  "rule": "AddFrameType(ft) appends ft as 2-octet big-endian (NOT the rest of the 36-octet frame header). AddTLV appends Type(2 BE)||Length(2 BE)||Value. A transcript point = SHA-256 over all bytes absorbed so far. Granularity is per-TLV (spec §3).",
  "spec": "N-PAMP draft-00 handshake binding (spec/10) §3 (transcript construction)"
